{"type":"text","timestamp":1775861992334,"sessionID":"ses_286630481ffeOc2rtsZEj0QW9M","part":{"id":"prt_d799dcd2f001mVf1LpQyAa8vlH","messageID":"msg_d799dabfe001gh7Xss7j8nrwfW","sessionID":"ses_286630481ffeOc2rtsZEj0QW9M","type":"text","text":"Now I'll write the delta-spec.md for AR-016 based on the proposal and following the same format as AR-015.","time":{"start":1775861992328,"end":1775861992328}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861992489,"sessionID":"ses_286630481ffeOc2rtsZEj0QW9M","part":{"id":"prt_d799f8b8b001ZhVu2inLZSd0X3","messageID":"msg_d799dabfe001gh7Xss7j8nrwfW","sessionID":"ses_286630481ffeOc2rtsZEj0QW9M","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-5d4389c40f8943d99594d11574aac4e5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nExtend PicoD's file management capabilities with comprehensive file system manipulation APIs including file deletion, directory creation, file copy/move, permissions modification, and archive operations (tar/zip) for AI agent workspace management. This builds upon AR-015's basic file operations (upload, list, download) with additional REST endpoints for full-featured workspace file management.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Delete request/response structures\n\nThe system SHALL define structures for file/directory deletion request and response.\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteRequest struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `DeleteRequest` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `Path string` with JSON tag `path` (wildcard path from URL)\n  - `Recursive bool` with JSON tag `recursive` (for directory deletion)\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteResponse struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `DeleteResponse` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `Path string` with JSON tag `path`\n  - `Deleted bool` with JSON tag `deleted`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Delete handler\n\nThe system SHALL implement file/directory deletion handler with recursive support.\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler path extraction\n- **GIVEN** DELETE request to `/api/files/*path`\n- **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `c.Param(\"path\")` SHALL extract wildcard path\n- AND leading `/` SHALL be stripped from path\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler path sanitization\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** processing delete path\n- **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, strippedPath)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler file existence check\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** checking path\n- **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if path not found\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler file deletion\n- **GIVEN** path is a regular file\n- **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `os.Remove(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `DeleteResponse`\n- AND `Deleted` SHALL be `true`\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler directory deletion with recursive flag\n- **GIVEN** path is a directory AND `Recursive` is `true`\n- **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `os.RemoveAll(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `DeleteResponse`\n- AND `Deleted` SHALL be `true`\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler directory deletion without recursive flag\n- **GIVEN** path is a directory AND `Recursive` is `false`\n- **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `os.Remove(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if directory is non-empty\n- AND error message SHALL indicate directory is not empty\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler empty directory deletion\n- **GIVEN** path is an empty directory AND `Recursive` is `false`\n- **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `os.Remove(sanitizedPath)` SHALL succeed\n- AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create directory request/response structures\n\nThe system SHALL define structures for directory creation request and response.\n\n#### Scenario: CreateDirectoryRequest struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `CreateDirectoryRequest` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `Path string` with JSON tag `path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n  - `Mode string` with JSON tag `mode` (optional octal string)\n\n#### Scenario: CreateDirectoryResponse struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `CreateDirectoryResponse` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `Path string` with JSON tag `path`\n  - `Mode string` with JSON tag `mode`\n  - `Created bool` with JSON tag `created`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create directory handler\n\nThe system SHALL implement directory creation handler with nested support.\n\n#### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler request binding\n- **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/directory`\n- **WHEN** CreateDirectoryHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `CreateDirectoryRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n\n#### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler path sanitization\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** processing directory path\n- **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Path)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n\n#### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler mode parsing\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** parsing directory mode\n- **THEN** `parseFileMode(req.Mode)` SHALL be called\n- AND default mode SHALL be `defaultDirMode` (`0755`) if mode empty/invalid\n\n#### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler nested directory creation\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** creating directory\n- **THEN** `os.MkdirAll(sanitizedPath, os.FileMode(mode))` SHALL be called\n- AND parent directories SHALL be created if not existing\n\n#### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler already exists\n- **GIVEN** directory already exists\n- **WHEN** CreateDirectoryHandler processes request\n- **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n- AND `Created` SHALL be `false`\n- AND existing directory mode SHALL be preserved\n\n#### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler response\n- **GIVEN** successful directory creation\n- **WHEN** CreateDirectoryHandler completes\n- **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n- AND `CreateDirectoryResponse` SHALL include path and mode\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Copy request/response structures\n\nThe system SHALL define structures for file/directory copy request and response.\n\n#### Scenario: CopyRequest struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `CopyRequest` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `Source string` with JSON tag `source` and `binding:\"required\"`\n  - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest` and `binding:\"required\"`\n\n#### Scenario: CopyResponse struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `CopyResponse` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `Source string` with JSON tag `source`\n  - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest`\n  - `Copied bool` with JSON tag `copied`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Copy handler\n\nThe system SHALL implement file/directory copy handler with recursive support.\n\n#### Scenario: CopyFileHandler request binding\n- **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/copy`\n- **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `CopyRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n\n#### Scenario: CopyFileHandler source sanitization\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** processing source path\n- **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Source)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n\n#### Scenario: CopyFileHandler destination sanitization\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** processing destination path\n- **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Dest)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n\n#### Scenario: CopyFileHandler source existence check\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** checking source path\n- **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n\n#### Scenario: CopyFileHandler file copy\n- **GIVEN** source is a regular file\n- **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `os.Open(source)` SHALL open source file\n- AND `os.Create(dest)` SHALL create destination file\n- AND `io.Copy(destFile, srcFile)` SHALL copy content\n- AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `CopyResponse`\n\n#### Scenario: CopyFileHandler directory copy\n- **GIVEN** source is a directory\n- **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `filepath.Walk(source, walkFunc)` SHALL be called\n- AND walkFunc SHALL copy each file to destination with relative path\n- AND directory structure SHALL be preserved\n- AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n\n#### Scenario: CopyFileHandler symlink handling\n- **GIVEN** source contains symlinks\n- **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** symlinks SHALL be skipped OR target SHALL be resolved\n- AND symlink escape SHALL be validated via `sanitizePath`\n\n#### Scenario: CopyFileHandler destination exists\n- **GIVEN** destination path already exists\n- **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n- AND error message SHALL indicate destination exists\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Move request/response structures\n\nThe system SHALL define structures for file/directory move request and response.\n\n#### Scenario: MoveRequest struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `MoveRequest` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `Source string` with JSON tag `source` and `binding:\"required\"`\n  - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest` and `binding:\"required\"`\n\n#### Scenario: MoveResponse struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `MoveResponse` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `Source string` with JSON tag `source`\n  - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest`\n  - `Moved bool` with JSON tag `moved`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Move handler\n\nThe system SHALL implement file/directory move/rename handler.\n\n#### Scenario: MoveFileHandler request binding\n- **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/move`\n- **WHEN** MoveFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `MoveRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n\n#### Scenario: MoveFileHandler source sanitization\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** processing source path\n- **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Source)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n\n#### Scenario: MoveFileHandler destination sanitization\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** processing destination path\n- **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Dest)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n\n#### Scenario: MoveFileHandler source existence check\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** checking source path\n- **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n\n#### Scenario: MoveFileHandler rename operation\n- **GIVEN** valid source and destination paths\n- **WHEN** MoveFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `os.Rename(sanitizedSource, sanitizedDest)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `MoveResponse`\n\n#### Scenario: MoveFileHandler cross-filesystem move\n- **GIVEN** source and destination on different filesystems\n- **WHEN** `os.Rename` returns cross-device error\n- **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n- AND error message SHALL indicate cross-filesystem move not supported\n\n#### Scenario: MoveFileHandler destination exists\n- **GIVEN** destination path already exists\n- **WHEN** MoveFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n- AND error message SHALL indicate destination exists\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Modify permissions request/response structures\n\nThe system SHALL define structures for permissions modification request and response.\n\n#### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsRequest struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `ModifyPermissionsRequest` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `Path string` with JSON tag `path` (wildcard path from URL)\n  - `Mode string` with JSON tag `mode` and `binding:\"required\"` (octal string)\n\n#### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsResponse struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `ModifyPermissionsResponse` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `Path string` with JSON tag `path`\n  - `OldMode string` with JSON tag `old_mode`\n  - `NewMode string` with JSON tag `new_mode`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Modify permissions handler\n\nThe system SHALL implement file/directory permissions modification handler.\n\n#### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler path extraction\n- **GIVEN** PATCH request to `/api/files/*path`\n- **WHEN** ModifyPermissionsHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `c.Param(\"path\")` SHALL extract wildcard path\n- AND leading `/` SHALL be stripped from path\n\n#### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler request binding\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** ModifyPermissionsHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `ModifyPermissionsRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n\n#### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler path sanitization\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** processing modify path\n- **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, strippedPath)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n\n#### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler file existence check\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** checking path\n- **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if path not found\n\n#### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler old mode retrieval\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** getting old permissions\n- **THEN** `info.Mode().Perm()` SHALL extract current mode\n- AND old mode SHALL be formatted as octal string\n\n#### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler mode parsing\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** parsing new mode\n- **THEN** `parseFileMode(req.Mode)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if mode invalid\n- AND mode SHALL be validated against `maxFileMode` (`0777`)\n\n#### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler chmod operation\n- **GIVEN** valid new mode\n- **WHEN** ModifyPermissionsHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `os.Chmod(sanitizedPath, os.FileMode(newMode))` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `ModifyPermissionsResponse`\n- AND response SHALL include old and new modes\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Archive request/response structures\n\nThe system SHALL define structures for archive creation request and response.\n\n#### Scenario: ArchiveRequest struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `ArchiveRequest` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n  - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n  - `Format string` with JSON tag `format` (optional: \"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\")\n\n#### Scenario: ArchiveResponse struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `ArchiveResponse` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path`\n  - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path`\n  - `Format string` with JSON tag `format`\n  - `Size int64` with JSON tag `size`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Archive handler\n\nThe system SHALL implement archive creation handler with tar/zip support.\n\n#### Scenario: ArchiveHandler request binding\n- **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/archive`\n- **WHEN** ArchiveHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `ArchiveRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n\n#### Scenario: ArchiveHandler source path sanitization\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** processing source path\n- **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.SourcePath)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n\n#### Scenario: ArchiveHandler destination path sanitization\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** processing destination path\n- **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.DestPath)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n\n#### Scenario: ArchiveHandler source existence check\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** checking source path\n- **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n\n#### Scenario: ArchiveHandler format detection\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** determining archive format\n- **THEN** format SHALL be detected from `req.Format` OR `filepath.Ext(req.DestPath)`\n- AND supported formats SHALL be `allowedArchiveFormats` (\"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\")\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned for unsupported format\n\n#### Scenario: ArchiveHandler tar creation\n- **GIVEN** format is \"tar\" or \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\"\n- **WHEN** ArchiveHandler creates archive\n- **THEN** `tar.Create` SHALL be used with `archive/tar` package\n- AND `filepath.Walk(source, walkFunc)` SHALL walk source\n- AND each entry SHALL be added with relative path\n- AND gzip SHALL be applied for \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\" format via `compress/gzip`\n\n#### Scenario: ArchiveHandler zip creation\n- **GIVEN** format is \"zip\"\n- **WHEN** ArchiveHandler creates archive\n- **THEN** `zip.Create` SHALL be used with `archive/zip` package\n- AND `filepath.Walk(source, walkFunc)` SHALL walk source\n- AND each entry SHALL be added with relative path\n\n#### Scenario: ArchiveHandler response\n- **GIVEN** successful archive creation\n- **WHEN** ArchiveHandler completes\n- **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n- AND `ArchiveResponse` SHALL include source path, destination path, format, and size\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Extract request/response structures\n\nThe system SHALL define structures for archive extraction request and response.\n\n#### Scenario: ExtractRequest struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `ExtractRequest` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n  - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path` (optional: defaults to parent directory)\n\n#### Scenario: ExtractResponse struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `ExtractResponse` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path`\n  - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path`\n  - `Files []FileEntry` with JSON tag `files` (extracted files list)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Extract handler\n\nThe system SHALL implement archive extraction handler with path escape protection.\n\n#### Scenario: ExtractHandler request binding\n- **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/extract`\n- **WHEN** ExtractHandler processes request\n- **THEN** `ExtractRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n\n#### Scenario: ExtractHandler source path sanitization\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** processing source path\n- **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.SourcePath)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n\n#### Scenario: ExtractHandler destination path resolution\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** `req.DestPath` is empty\n- **THEN** `filepath.Dir(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be used as destination\n- WHEN `req.DestPath` is non-empty\n- **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.DestPath)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n\n#### Scenario: ExtractHandler source existence check\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** checking source path\n- **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n- AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n\n#### Scenario: ExtractHandler size limit check\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** checking archive size\n- **THEN** `os.Stat(source).Size()` SHALL get archive size\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if size > `maxArchiveSize` (`100 << 20`)\n- AND error message SHALL indicate archive exceeds size limit\n\n#### Scenario: ExtractHandler format detection\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** determining archive format\n- **THEN** format SHALL be detected from `filepath.Ext(req.SourcePath)`\n- AND supported formats SHALL be `allowedArchiveFormats`\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned for unsupported format\n\n#### Scenario: ExtractHandler tar extraction\n- **GIVEN** format is \"tar\" or \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\"\n- **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts archive\n- **THEN** `tar.NewReader` SHALL be used with `archive/tar` package\n- AND gzip SHALL be decompressed for \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\" via `compress/gzip`\n- AND each entry SHALL be extracted to destination\n\n#### Scenario: ExtractHandler zip extraction\n- **GIVEN** format is \"zip\"\n- **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts archive\n- **THEN** `zip.OpenReader` SHALL be used with `archive/zip` package\n- AND each entry SHALL be extracted to destination\n\n#### Scenario: ExtractHandler entry path sanitization\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** extracting each archive entry\n- **THEN** `sanitizePath(destination, entry.Name)` SHALL be called for each entry path\n- AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if entry path escapes workspace\n- AND entry path SHALL reject `..` components\n\n#### Scenario: ExtractHandler directory entry creation\n- **GIVEN** archive entry is a directory\n- **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts entry\n- **THEN** `os.MkdirAll(entryPath, entry.Mode)` SHALL create directory\n- AND nested directories SHALL be created\n\n#### Scenario: ExtractHandler file entry creation\n- **GIVEN** archive entry is a file\n- **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts entry\n- **THEN** `os.Create(entryPath)` SHALL create file\n- AND entry content SHALL be written via `io.Copy`\n- AND file mode SHALL be set via `os.Chmod`\n\n#### Scenario: ExtractHandler response\n- **GIVEN** successful extraction\n- **WHEN** ExtractHandler completes\n- **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n- AND `ExtractResponse` SHALL include source path, destination path, and extracted files list\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Route registration extension\n\nThe system SHALL extend route registration with new file management endpoints.\n\n#### Scenario: New file management routes registration\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n- **WHEN** registering routes\n- **THEN** `/api/files/*path` SHALL be registered with `DeleteFileHandler` (DELETE)\n- AND `/api/files/directory` SHALL be registered with `CreateDirectoryHandler` (POST)\n- AND `/api/files/copy` SHALL be registered with `CopyFileHandler` (POST)\n- AND `/api/files/move` SHALL be registered with `MoveFileHandler` (POST)\n- AND `/api/files/*path` SHALL be registered with `ModifyPermissionsHandler` (PATCH)\n- AND `/api/files/archive` SHALL be registered with `ArchiveHandler` (POST)\n- AND `/api/files/extract` SHALL be registered with `ExtractHandler` (POST)\n- AND all routes SHALL use existing JWT auth middleware\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Constants\n\nThe system SHALL define constants for file management behavior configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: defaultDirMode constant\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- **WHEN** reading constants\n- **THEN** `defaultDirMode` SHALL be `0755`\n\n#### Scenario: maxArchiveSize constant\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** reading constants\n- **THEN** `maxArchiveSize` SHALL be `100 << 20` (100 MiB)\n\n#### Scenario: allowedArchiveFormats constant\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n- **WHEN** reading constants\n- **THEN** `allowedArchiveFormats` SHALL be `[\"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\"]`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle errors with appropriate HTTP status codes and messages.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete non-empty directory without recursive error\n- **GIVEN** directory is non-empty AND `Recursive` is `false`\n- **WHEN** delete fails\n- **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n- AND body SHALL indicate directory is not empty\n\n#### Scenario: Cross-filesystem move error\n- **GIVEN** `os.Rename` returns cross-device error\n- **WHEN** MoveFileHandler encounters error\n- **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n- AND body SHALL indicate cross-filesystem move not supported\n\n#### Scenario: Archive size exceeded error\n- **GIVEN** archive size > `maxArchiveSize`\n- **WHEN** ExtractHandler detects size violation\n- **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n- AND body SHALL indicate archive exceeds size limit\n\n#### Scenario: Unsupported archive format error\n- **GIVEN** unsupported archive format\n- **WHEN** ArchiveHandler or ExtractHandler detects format\n- **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n- AND body SHALL indicate unsupported format\n\n#### Scenario: Archive entry path escape error\n- **GIVEN** archive entry path escapes workspace\n- **WHEN** ExtractHandler detects path escape\n- **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n- AND body SHALL indicate invalid entry path\n\n---\n\n## Constants Summary\n\n| Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|------|---------|\n| `defaultDirMode` | `0755` | `files.go` | Default directory creation mode |\n| `maxArchiveSize` | `100 << 20` | `archive.go` | Maximum archive size for extraction (100 MiB) |\n| `allowedArchiveFormats` | `[\"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\"]` | `archive.go` | Supported archive formats |\n\n---\n\n## API Endpoints Summary\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Auth | Handler |\n|----------|--------|------|---------|\n| `/api/files/*path` | DELETE | JWT | `DeleteFileHandler` |\n| `/api/files/directory` | POST | JWT | `CreateDirectoryHandler` |\n| `/api/files/copy` | POST | JWT | `CopyFileHandler` |\n| `/api/files/move` | POST | JWT | `MoveFileHandler` |\n| `/api/files/*path` | PATCH | JWT | `ModifyPermissionsHandler` |\n| `/api/files/archive` | POST | JWT | `ArchiveHandler` |\n| `/api/files/extract` | POST | JWT | `ExtractHandler` |\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `pkg/picod/files.go` | Extend | Add `DeleteRequest`, `DeleteResponse`, `CreateDirectoryRequest`, `CreateDirectoryResponse`, `CopyRequest`, `CopyResponse`, `MoveRequest`, `MoveResponse`, `ModifyPermissionsRequest`, `ModifyPermissionsResponse`, and handlers |\n| `pkg/picod/archive.go` | Create | `ArchiveRequest`, `ArchiveResponse`, `ExtractRequest`, `ExtractResponse`, `ArchiveHandler`, `ExtractHandler` |\n| `pkg/picod/server.go` | Extend | Register new file management routes |\n| `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Extend | Unit tests for new handlers |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- `changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md` — Original PicoD implementation\n- `pkg/picod/sanitize.go` — Path security logic\n- [Go archive/tar](https://pkg.go.dev/archive/tar)\n- [Go archive/zip](https://pkg.go.dev/archive/zip)\n- [Go compress/gzip](https://pkg.go.dev/compress/gzip)"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775861992460,"end":1775861992486}}}}
